716545f-a.title: Manhattan: Battery Park - Battery Place and West Street.
716545f-a.text:
Battery Park: It's Embarkerdero and moored excursion
steamers. Thru the center appears a glimpse of the
ACuarium. The Whitehall Bldg. is at the northwesterly
confine of the Park, being at Battery Place and West St.
A section of Jersey City is at the left margin, separated
from New York City by the North(Hudson) River.
1939
Alexander Alland
NO REPRODUCTI13
